   But the request has been stalled by Senate Democrats, some of whom believe that Eastern Europe has a greater claim on U.S. resources than Nicaragua.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Wells' nomination as ambassador to Mozambique in 1986 encountered strong opposition from Senate conservatives who held up the appointment for 11 months in protest against U.S. policy toward that country.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   Sen. Jesse Helms, R-N.C.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
